  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Obese patients may have difficulty in airway management.Patients who have body mass index &gt;
      35 are challenging patients for anesthesiologist. Short neck, more adipose tissue may be
      reasons for airway difficulty. Videolaryngoscopes are devices that ease the management of
      difficult airway.This study is designed to evaluate the differences and the effects of
      different laryngoscopes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
